===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: from a pictograph of a pregnant woman. See also the reversed version [[㐆]]. Unrelated to [[射]].

===Etymology 1===
STEDT relates it to {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*sja-n ~ sin|*sja-n ~ *sin|flesh; animal; body}}, but recent {{cog|och|-}} reconstructions would not support this etymology.

Because {{lang|zh|身}} is used as a phonetic for {{och-l|仁|tr=*niŋ}} in excavated texts, {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2012, 2014)}} reconstruct the initial as nasal. This would allow for a comparison to {{cog|bo|སྙིང||heart}}, {{cog|sit-jap|tɯ'''sni'''||heart}} ({{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2012}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques and Lai, 2019}}), which are from {{cog|sit-pro|*s-niŋ||heart; mind; brain}}.

